1-Download Arduino IDE.
2- Run Arduino IDE.
3- Click file and preferences.
4- Put the package link to the esp32: https://dl.espressif.com/dl/package_esp32_index.json press ok.
5- Click Tools Board: Arduino Uno, Board manager.
 6- Write esp32 and install.
7- Go to the tools, Board: Arduino Uno, Esp32 Arduino 
8- Connect ESP32 to the USP to the computer.
9- Go to tools, Board: Arduino Uno, Esp32 Arduino, WEMOS D1 MINI ESP32
10- Than go to tools port:COM3, COM3
11- For to turn on lighting: Choose file, examples, Basics and Blink
